args: Aeleen is a warrior. And while her soul is kind,\nwhen she gets into a fight...
YOU ARE ALL GOING TO DIIIIIE!

Er, well, she tends to lose her temper—hence
her reputation as a warrior with whom one does
not want to pick a fight. But the way of war was
not always her chosen life's pursuit...
You want to become a NURSE?!
Yes. It's long been a dream of mine.
Why are you all looking at me like that?\nIs it really such a strange request?
N-not at all! It just comes as something\nof a surprise, is all.
We certainly aren't thinking that nurse\nis a WILDLY inappropriate profession\nfor one of your temperament.
Er, maybe you should take a step back\nand tell us where this idea came from.
I suppose I DID spring it on you\nout of the blue...
Well, as you know, I currently follow\nthe path of the warrior.
But ever since I was young,\nI've always wanted to be a nurse.
A kindly one who can see people through\nsickness and help with their injuries.
There was a hospital in my hometown,\nso I'm quite familiar with nurses and the\nimportant work they do.
I often saw them walking around in their\nspotless white coats—it seemed every\nchild looked up to them.
Sounds like quite the popular profession.\nBut if that was your dream, how did you\nend up becoming a warrior?
My village's vigilante militia apparently\nthought I had what it took.
I couldn't bring myself to turn them down\nwhen they asked me to join, and before I\nknew it, I'd been with them for years.
That's surprising. I figured you became a\nwarrior by choice, not because others\nhad to talk you into it.
Still, it's easy to see why they pursued you.\nYou possess a natural talent for combat.
However, it is very Aeleen for you to have\nfought this whole time while also being\nrather opposed to the entire enterprise.
Oh, I don't regret becoming a warrior.
I've been able to protect a lot of important\nthings as a result, which is great.
Still, this castle has plenty of warriors.
So I thought now would be a good time\nto try and achieve my true dream.
Well, I think it's a fine idea.
I, for one, would love some help dealing\nwith the injured in our makeshift infirmary.
You're very knowledgeable on medical\nherbs, so I know you'll be a fine asset.
Thank you, everyone. I won't let you down!
Truthfully, I've long thought that I'd be\nbetter suited to medical arts than combat!
Oh dear. You're looking at me again.
N-no we're not! We're just, um... Hahaha...
We're all very happy for you, Aeleen.
However, if you plan to start this new\npath in your life, I have a little present\nto help get you started.
I think it suits you perfectly.
Thank you! I felt like a real nurse\nthe moment I put it on.
Now I can finally get down\nto the business of healing!
It will certainly put patients more at ease\nthan if you did your rounds in armor.
Still, as nursing is traditionally a human\nprofession, I had to copy other uniforms\nwhile making it, so I'm glad you like it.
Like I said, I won't let you down!
I'm going to be a kindly nurse who\nsupports everyone from the sidelines!
We can't wait to see you in action.
I'm in the middle of seeing a patient here,\nbut I guess I'll just have to bump YOU up\nto the front of the line!
Er, wasn't the plan to be a kindly nurse\nwho stayed on the sidelines...?
You suggested the other day that you\nare not truly suited to the rigors of battle,\nbut I do not believe that is the case.
I don't think there are many others who\ncould be so deadly with a staff...
It just startled me is all!
Give me another chance! Please!\nI KNOW I can learn to be kind!
